## It's a Bust
Yeah bad news, the thing that always happens happened again and I lost interest in the game so there will be no more **Mail Thief** thank god the domain name was taken when I tried to look for it. This domain however will stay mine methinks. 

## Post mortem
A couple things went wrong here, and I'm not even sure using the term "went wrong" is the correct strategy. In essence what I developed was a prototype for a game and it turns out it wasn't very fun. I don't think that's a failure. One thing that I'm definitely going to be aware of going forward is that I do not enjoy playing story-based games so I probably am not going to enjoy making a game where the entire thing behind it is based on me creating dozens of stories (that was a terrible idea). 

### Happy Things
I am still planning on participating in an upcoming game jam in 2 days (oh god) and currently it looks like I'll be approaching it solo. This is a very short game jam and I'm working half the days so I will be forced to make my scope TINY

Also, I appreciated learning more about Godot! I like this game engine more than any game engine I've used so far and expect to continue using it moving forward. That's all for today.